               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17310428-64-person344">
                  George 
                  Dawson 
               <interp inst="t17310428-64-person344" type="surname" value="Dawson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-64-person344" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-64-person344" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That the Prisoner did entice and encourage Boys to go a thieving, lodg'd them in her House, and us'd to give them what she pleas'd for the Things they stole, and then made them spend the Money at her House; that she bought the Hock of Bacon that he had stolen from Mr. Godfrey, and also a Gammon of Bacon of 18 Pound, for which she gave them 3 s.</p>
               <p>- Perkins depos'd, That he stole Mr. Low's Cheese, and carried it to her, and she gave him 18 pence for it, and they spent the Money in Gin. and Hot-Pots, at her House; that he stole half a Firkin of Soap, and sold it to her for 3 s.</p>
               <p>These Evidences were very little Boys of about 12 Years of Age (as they said) tho' by their Stature one would have taken them not to be above 8 or 9.</p>
               <p>The several Facts being prov'd to the Satisfaction of the Jury, they found her <rs id="t17310428-64-verdict321" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17310428-64-verdict321" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of the Indictment.</p>
